Following his strike against the Great Danes, the Anglo-Nigerian, Tammy Abraham, has joined the list of players who scored on their birthday in the competition. <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1264727" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Tammy.jpg?resize=300%2C200&#038;ssl=1" alt="Chelsea, Abraham, Sterling" width="300" height="200" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Tammy.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Tammy.jpg?resize=768%2C513&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Tammy.jpg?resize=1024%2C683&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Tammy.jpg?resize=58%2C39&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Tammy.jpg?resize=260%2C174&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Tammy.jpg?resize=195%2C130&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Tammy.jpg?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Tammy.jpg?resize=560%2C374&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Tammy.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Tammy.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Birthday boy Tammy Abraham has joined Manchester City’s Raheem Sterling in exclusive Champions League ranks.
The Chelsea forward opened his account in the competition with his effort against Lille at Stade Pierre-Mauroy. ALSO READ: VAR to the rescue as Arsenal hold Manchester United in Old Trafford Abraham fired past Mike Maignana in the 22nd minute after taking down an excellent cross from Fikayo Tomori. With that, he becomes the second English player to score in the Champions League on their birthday after Manchester City’s Sterling against Borussia Monchengladbach in December 2015. Also, he combined with Tomori to equal Frank Lampard and John Terry’s seven-year record, being the first time two English players scored and assisted in the elite tournament. The Stamford Bridge giants travel to Ajax on October 23 for their next Champions League fixture, Goal reported. Vanguard Frank Lampard said Chelsea's transfer embargo did not force his hand to play young forward Tammy Abraham, who has surged to the top of the Premier League goalscoring charts. September 16, 2019 In "News" Record Manchester City signing Rodri made his debut and Raheem Sterling scored twice as the Premier League champions came from behind to beat West Ham United 4-1 on Wednesday in China. July 17, 2019 In "News" Tammy Abraham grabbed his first Chelsea hat-trick as Chelsea eased past Wolves 5-2 in the Premier League to return to winning ways. September 14, 2019 In "News"